# Codebase Structure

When making changes, follow the folder conventions in the project root AGENTS.md.

## Hooks Placement

- **`src/hooks/`** — Page-level: route params, page data, redirects. Used by multiple pages.
- **`components/<feature>/hooks/`** — Feature-specific: colocate with the feature.

Do not add feature-specific hooks to `src/hooks/`. Use the feature's `hooks/` folder.

## Key Folders

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `pages/` | Thin route wrappers. Delegate to content components. |
| `components/tasks/` | Today page, daily tasks, journal, one-time tasks |
| `components/activities/` | Groups, activities, timelines, archive |
| `components/settings/` | Auth, backup, sync, appearance |
| `components/ui/` | Shared UI primitives (button, card, input, etc.) |
| `lib/` | DB, sync, utilities. Single source for shared logic. |

Read the folder's `CONTEXT.md` for details when working in that area.
